The '''Drama-Logue Award''' was an American [[Theatre|theater]] award established in 1977, given by the publishers of [[Backstage (magazine)#Drama-Logue|Drama-Logue]] newspaper, a weekly west-coast theater [[Trade journal|trade publication]].<ref name="LATimes_24May1998_Theater_DemiseofDrama-Logue">{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1998/may/24/entertainment/ca-52984|title=Assessing the Demise of Drama-Logue - Los Angeles Times|last=Shirley|first=Don|date=24 May 1998|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|accessdate=29 September 2010}}</ref>  Winners were selected by the publication's theater critics, and would receive a certificate at an annual awards ceremony.  The award categories included [[Theatrical producer|Production]], [[Theatre director|Direction]], [[Music director|Musical Direction]], [[Choreography]], [[Playwright|Writing]], [[Actor|Performance]], [[Ensemble cast|Ensemble Performance]], [[Scenic Design]], [[Sound Design]], [[Lighting Design]], [[Costume Design]] and [[Cosmetology|Hair & Makeup Design]].

==Acquisition ==
In May 1998, ''[[Backstage (magazine)|Backstage West]]'' bought the Drama-Logue publication, and the two publications merged. The Drama-Logue Awards were subsequently retired and replaced by the [[Back Stage West Garland Awards]].<ref name="LATimes_24May1998_Theater_DemiseofDrama-Logue"/>

