'''KAONMEDIA''' (or KAON Media Co Ltd) is a [[South Korea]]n technology company<ref name="Reuters company info">{{cite news|title=KAON Media Co Ltd (078890.KQ)|url=http://in.reuters.com/finance/stocks/companyProfile?symbol=078890.KQ|accessdate=15 July 2014|publisher=Reuters}}</ref><ref name="Company Ltd">{{cite web|title=Kaonmedia Co., Ltd.|url=https://www.google.co.uk/finance?cid=697400911085369|website=[[Google Finance]]|accessdate=15 July 2014}}</ref> which specialises in the development and manufacturing of digital connectivity devices (including [[set-top box]]es) and [[residential gateway]]s for [[Pay television|pay-TV operator]], [[Wireless Internet service provider|broadband operators]] and [[Telephone company|telcos]]. It provides digital broadcasting services to more than 120 operators in 80 countries. The company is based in [[Seongnam|Sungnam]] city, South Korea and was founded in 2001.
In November 2013 KAONMEDIA announced that it has started to provide [[Android (operating system)|Android]] set-top boxes, with the latest Google services for TV, on South Korean broadband; this is the world's first commercial launch of IPTV with the latest Android OS (Jellybean 4.2).<ref name=Android>{{cite web|title=SK broadband launches Android IPTV STB from KAON|url=http://www.digitaltvnews.net/?p=23267|website=digitaltvnews.net|accessdate=13 November 2013}}</ref>
